com.ikueb.mapextractor

Class MapExtractor.Parser<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ikueb.mapextractor.MapExtractor.Parser<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - the desired key type
    V - the desired value type
    Enclosing class:
    MapExtractor

    public static final class MapExtractor.Parser<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
    A class meant for parsing CharSequences to Maps. Whereas the main MapExtractor utility class adheres more closely to line-based processing, where each stream element is a line, this uses the notion of 'records', where a stream element may contain more than one record. This is useful for facilitating quick, 'one-shot' CharSequence-to-Map conversions.

    Implementation notes:

    • The underlying transformation is done using a Stream.flatMap(Function), so it does not directly use the Collector implementations of MapExtractor. However, certain underlying fields and methods are reused and will be pointed out where appropriate.
    • The Function for performing the flat-mapping and Collector are defined during instantiation.
    • Owing to how functions and collectors are currently non-comparable (in layman terms), instances of this class should not be used in a similar manner as well.
